{"0":"All three output files are correctly generated. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n## Results Summary\n\n### What the scheduler did\n\n1. **Parsed all inputs** — 30 existing events (no conflicts found among originals), 15 new requests, and the constraints from `constraints.yaml` (Asia/Shanghai timezone, 12:00–13:00 lunch block, 4-meeting daily cap, attendee unavailability rules).\n\n2. **Sorted requests by priority** (P0→P1→P2, earlier window first) and greedily assigned the earliest valid slot in each preferred window.\n\n3. **10 of 15 requests scheduled** (total priority weight: 26/43 maximum):\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | Scheduled Time (CST) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| req_004 | Vision Demo Rehearsal | **P0** | Apr 14 11:00–12:00 |\n| req_006 | Offline Eval Deep Dive | **P0** | Apr 15 10:00–11:30 |\n| req_002 | Dataset Labeling Escalation | P1 | Apr 13 13:00–13:30 |\n| req_005 | Red Team Security Review | P1 | Apr 14 13:30–14:30 |\n| req_009 | Infra Cost Reduction Workshop | P1 | Apr 16 13:00–14:30 |\n| req_012 | Compliance Follow-up | P1 | Apr 17 13:30–14:00 |\n| req_003 | Q2 Budget Alignment | P2 | Apr 13 09:00–09:45 |\n| req_007 | Hiring Panel Calibration | P2 | Apr 15 14:30–15:15 |\n| req_010 | Design Partner Feedback Review | P2 | Apr 16 15:00–16:00 |\n| req_015 | Ops Overflow Triage | P2 | Apr 14 17:30–18:00 |\n\n4. **5 requests could not be scheduled:**\n   - **req_001** (P0) — alice & bob both have back-to-back existing meetings in all preferred windows\n   - **req_011** (P0) — alice already at 3 meetings on Friday; her preferred window (10:30–12:00) overlaps existing Engineering Standup\n   - **req_014** (P1) — alice is unavailable all day Wednesday (hard constraint)\n   - **req_008** (P1) — alice is unavailable all day Wednesday (hard constraint)\n   - **req_013** (P2) — frank is unavailable Friday 17:00–23:59 (hard constraint)","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.1","hostname":"1ca337e14a11","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-06-